  "prompt": "What is the best pancake recipe that doesn't use baking powder?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a delicious pancake recipe that doesn't use baking powder, you can achieve light and fluffy pancakes by relying on other leavening agents or techniques. Here's a simple and reliable recipe using **self-rising flour** (which already contains a leavening agent) or a **yogurt and baking soda** combination for fluffiness:\n\n### **No-Baking-Powder Pancakes**\n\n#### Ingredients:\n- 1 cup (125g) self-rising flour **(OR 1 cup all-purpose flour + 1/2 teaspoon baking soda if using yogurt)**\n- 1 tablespoon granulated sugar (optional, for sweetness)\n- 1 large egg\n- 3/4 cup (180ml) milk (adjust for desired thickness)\n- 1 tablespoon melted butter or oil (plus extra for cooking)\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 cup (60g) plain yogurt **(only if using all-purpose flour)**  \n- A splash of vanilla extract (optional, for flavor)\n\n---\n\n#### Instructions:\n1. **If using self-rising flour:**  \n   - In a large bowl, whisk together the self-rising flour, sugar, and salt.\n\n2. **If using all-purpose flour:**  \n   - In a large bowl, whisk together the all-purpose flour, baking soda, sugar, and salt.  \n   - In a separate bowl, mix the yogurt and milk until smooth.  \n\n3. **Make the batter:**  \n   - In a separate bowl, whisk the egg, milk (or yogurt-milk mixture), melted butter, and vanilla extract (if using).  \n   - Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Don\u2019t overmix\u2014small lumps are fine.  \n\n4. **Cook the pancakes:**  \n   - Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. Add a little butter or oil to coat the surface.  \n   - Pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges look set (about 2-3 minutes).  \n   - Flip and cook for another 1-2 minutes until golden brown.  \n\n5. **Serve:**  \n   - Stack the pancakes and serve warm with your favorite toppings, like maple syrup, fresh fruit, or whipped cream.\n\n---\n\nThis recipe results in fluffy and tender pancakes without the need for baking powder. Enjoy! \ud83e\udd5e\u2728",
